comments: Conflicting evidence: felicitous in Q1, infelicitous in Q2 without continuation.
Conflicting evidence: infelicitous in Q2, but noted as potentially felicitous with continuation.
Evidence shows single 'ite' can be felicitous (GR-EVD-074), but 'ite...ite' in same context is infelicitous (GR-EVD-073).
Judgment is 'felicitous' in Q1 but '?' in Q2, with comments noting it is dispreferred.
